							<h3>Waterworks Clarifier Tank - Beach Replacement Design</h3>
							<p>Tom was commissioned by a steel fabricator & site services provider to visit a water treatment works to survey an existing set of scum beaches installed in a decommissioned clarifier tank, with a view to removing & replacing with new as a stage in recommissioning the tank.</p>
							<p>The existing design had to be surveyed in detail, including the main mild steel sheet fabrications which were badly worn & corroded, as well as the support bracketry and connecting pipework. He reverse-engineered a new replacement design to meet the same functional requirements, but in a way that was much simplified, easier to install, more robust & lower-cost than the original.</p>
							<p>He produced 3D models (existing & proposed), general arrangement drawings and a full manufacturing drawing pack from which the fabricator worked to build & install the new equipment. The refurbishment project was carried out successfully first time with no TQ's, making way for the end-client to bring their clarifier tank back into full operation.</p>
