						<div class="col-12 col-md-8">
							<h3>Storage Silo - Rupture Panel Support Frame Design</h3>
							<p>Rupture panels are sacrificial foil 'windows' fitted to storage silos that are designed to break before internal pressure reaches a dangerous level, which relieves the pressure & prevents an explosion. Several large biomass storage silos required rupture panels to be installed facing upwards on a reinforced concrete roof structure.</p>
							<p>Tom was asked to come up with a design solution to mount multiple panels onto robust but cost-effective frames that could be assembled at ground level and then lifted into place & cast into the concrete roof. He generated several concept options, carried out structural analysis & verification, and then developed full manufacturing detail designs to meet a very challenging project timetable.</p>
							<p>The final design was a bespoke welded platework fabrication. Each module had more than 20 rupture panels, a central walkway, fall-protection beneath each panel and hand-railing all round. Twelve frames in total were manufactured, tested and successfully installed on the silo roofs.</p>
